@newservermaker wrote:

[quote=“aftereffect, post:1, topic:148797”]Wow you people don’t know java worth of shit if your giving him responses like this. To fix this problem you case needs to be in a switch statement, for example:

public void bla() { case 1: break; }Would give that error, this on the other hand wont,

public void bla() { switch(150) { // Just an example case 1: break; } } Remember this is just an example so your going to need to find where that case belongs.[/quote]

thats what i seid… he needs to add a } or more…
